===Tardigrades=== [[Tardigrade]] species identified in recent research:<ref name="adams" /> {{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Acutuncus antarcticus]]'' *''[[Diphascon]]'' spp. (form. ''[[Adropoion]]'' spp.) **''[[Diphascon alpinum]]'' **''[[Diphascon dastychi]]'' **''[[Diphascon polare]]'' **''[[Diphascon tricuspidatum]]'' (form. ''[[Adropion tricuspidatum]]'') **''[[Diphascon victoriae]]'' *''[[Hypsibius]]'' spp. (form. ''[[Diphascon]]'' spp.) **''[[Hypsibius alpinus]]'' **''[[Hypsibius arcticus]]'' **[[Hypsibius cfr mertoni simoizumii|''Hypsibius'' cfr ''mertoni simoizumii'']] **''[[Hypsibius convergens]]'' **''[[Hypsibius oberhaeseri]]'' **''[[Hypsibius scoticus]]'' (form. ''[[Diphascon scoticus]]'') *''[[Macrobiotus arcticus]]'' *''[[Macrobiotus cfr polaris]]'' *''[[Macrobiotus mottai]]'' *''[[Macrobiotus oberhauseri]]'' *''[[Macrobiotus polaris]]'' *''[[Minibiotus furcatus]]'' *''[[Ramajendas frigidus]]'' *''[[Ramazzottius]]'' spp. **''[[Ramazzottius oberhauseri]]'' {{div col end}}
==Bacteria== Typically, the highest numbers of cultured [[bacteria]] are from relatively moist coastal soils, compared with the small bacteria communities of dry inland soils.<ref name="adams" /> [[Cyanobacteria]] are found in all types of aquatic habitats and often dominate the microbial biomass of streams and lake sediments.<ref name="adams" /> ''[[Leptolyngbya frigida]]'' is dominant in benthic mats, and is frequently found in soils and as an [[epiphyte]] on [[moss]]es.<ref name="adams" /> [[Nostoc commune var. sphaeroides|''Nostoc commune'']] can develop to sizes visible to the naked eye if supplied with a thin water film.<ref name="adams" /> The genus ''[[Gloeocapsa]]'' is one of the few [[Endolith#Subdefinitions|cryptoendolithic]] taxa with a high adaptation to extreme environmental conditions in rocks of the [[McMurdo Dry Valleys|Dry Valleys]].<ref name="adams" /> [[Actinobacteria]] such as ''[[Arthrobacter]]'' spp., ''[[Brevibacterium]]'' spp., and ''[[Corynebacterium]]'' spp. are prominent in the Dry Valleys.<ref name="cary" /> [[Thermophile|Thermophilic]] bacteria have been isolated from thermally heated soils near [[Mount Melbourne|Mt. Melbourne]] and Mt. Rittman in northern [[Victoria Land]].<ref name="adams">{{cite journal |last1=Adams |first1=B.J. |year=2006 |title=Diversity and distribution of Victoria Land biota |url= |journal=Soil Biology & Biochemistry |volume=38 |issue=10 |pages=3003–3018 |doi=10.1016/j.soilbio.2006.04.030}}</ref> Bacteria genera found in both air samples and the [[Antarctic]] include ''[[Staphylococcus]]'', ''[[Bacillus]]'', ''[[Corynebacterium]]'', ''[[Micrococcus]]'', ''[[Streptococcus]]'', ''[[Neisseria]]'', and ''[[Pseudomonas]]''.<ref name="pearce">{{cite journal |last1=Pearce |first1=D.A. | display-authors = etal |year=2009 |title=Microorganims in the atmosphere over Antarctica |url= |journal=FEMS Microbiology Ecology |volume=69 |issue=2 |pages=143–157 |doi=10.1111/j.1574-6941.2009.00706.x |pmid=19527292}}</ref>
[[Bacteria]] species identified in recent research:<ref name="adams" /> {{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Acinetobacter]]'' spp. *''[[Alicyclobacillus acidocaldarius]]'' *''[[Aquaspirillum]]'' spp. *''[[Arthrobacter]]'' spp. *''[[Azospirillum]]'' spp. *''[[Bacillus]]'' spp. **''[[Bacillus fumarioli]]'' **''[[Bacillus thermoantarcticus]]'' *''[[Bizionia argentinensis]]''<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Bercovich|first=Andrés|last2=Vazquez|first2=Susana C.|last3=Yankilevich|first3=Patricio|last4=Coria|first4=Silvia H.|last5=Foti|first5=Marcelo|last6=Hernández|first6=Edgardo|last7=Vidal|first7=Alejandro|last8=Ruberto|first8=Lucas|last9=Melo|first9=Carlos|date=2008|title=''Bizionia argentinensis'' sp. nov., isolated from surface marine water in Antarctica|journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology|volume=58|issue=10|pages=2363–2367|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.65599-0|pmid=18842857}}</ref> *''[[Brevibacterium]]'' spp. **''[[Brevibacterium antarcticum]]'' *''[[Brevundimonas]]'' spp. *''[[Chryseobacterium]]'' spp. *''[[Corynebacterium]]'' spp. *''[[Flavobacterium]]'' spp. *''[[Gloeocapsa]]'' spp. *''[[Hymenobacter roseosalivarius]]'' *''[[Leptolyngbya frigida]]'' *''[[Massila]]'' spp. *''[[Micrococcus]]'' spp. *''[[Modestobacter multiseptatus]]'' *''[[Neisseria]]'' spp. *''[[Nocardia]]'' spp. *''[[Nostoc commune]]'' *''[[Paenibacillus]]'' spp. *''[[Planococcus]]'' spp. *''[[Pseudonocardia antarctica]]'' *''[[Pseudomonas]]'' spp. *''[[Psychrobacter]]'' spp. *''[[Sphingobacterium]]'' spp. *''[[Staphylococcus]]'' spp. *''[[Stenotrophomonas]]'' spp. *''[[Streptococcus]]'' spp. *''[[Streptomyces]]'' spp. {{div col end}}
==Fungi== ''[[Chaetomium gracile]]'' is frequently isolated from geothermally heated soil on [[Mount Melbourne|Mt. Melbourne]] in northern [[Victoria Land]].<ref name="adams" /> Fungi genera found in both air samples and the [[Antarctic]] include ''[[Penicillium]]'', ''[[Aspergillus]]'', ''[[Cladosporium]]'', ''[[Alternaria]]'', ''[[Aureobasidium]]'', ''[[Botryotrichum]]'', ''[[Botrytis (fungus)|Botrytis]]'', ''[[Geotrichum]]'', ''[[Staphylotrichum]]'', ''[[Paecilomyces]]'', and ''[[Rhizopus]]''.<ref name="pearce" />
[[Fungus|Fungi]] species identified in recent research:<ref name="adams" /><ref name=arenz11>{{cite journal |date=2011 |title=Fungal colonization of exotic substrates in Antarctica |journal=Fungal Diversity |doi=10.1007/s13225-010-0079-4 |url=http://forestpathology.cfans.umn.edu/pdf/Fungal%20colonization%20of%20exotic%20substrates%20in%20Antarctica.pdf |author=Arenz, B. E. |author2=B. W. Held |author3=J. A. Jurgens |author4=R. A. Blanchette| last-author-amp=yes |volume=49 |pages=13–22}}</ref> {{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Alternaria]]'' spp. *''[[Antarctomyces psychotrophicus]]'' *''[[Arthrobotrys ferox]]'' *''[[Aspergillus]]'' spp. **''[[Aspergillus ustus]]'' *''[[Aureobasidium]]'' spp. *''[[Botryotrichum]]'' spp. *''[[Botrytis (fungus)|Botrytis]]'' spp. *''[[Chaetomium gracile]]'' *''[[Cadophora]]'' ssp. **''[[Cadophora malorum]]'' *''[[Cerrena unicolor]]'' *''[[Cladosporium]]'' spp. **''[[Cladosporium cladosporioides]]'' **''[[Cladosporium herbarum]]'' *''[[Cochliobolus heliconiae]]'' *''[[Coniochaeta ligniaria]]'' *''[[Curvularia inaequalis]]'' *''[[Debaryomyces]]'' ssp. **''[[Debaryomyces hansenii]]'' *''[[Geomyces]]'' spp. **''[[Geomyces pannorum]]'' (form. ''[[Chrysosporium pannorum]]'') *''[[Geotrichum]]'' spp. *''[[Hohenbuehelia]]'' spp. *''[[Holwaya mucida]]'' *''[[Mortierella antarctica]]'' *''[[Mucor hiemalis]]'' *''[[Paecilomyces]]'' spp. *''[[Penicillium]]'' spp. **''[[Penicillium jensenii]]'' **''[[Penicillium swiecickii]]'' *''[[Phaeosphaeria]]'' spp. *''[[Phialophora]]'' spp. **''[[Phialophora fastigiata]]'' (form. ''[[Cadophora fastigiata]]'') *''[[Phoma]]'' spp. **''[[Phoma herbarum]]'' *''[[Rhizopus]]'' spp. *''[[Rhizoscyphus ericae]]'' *''[[Staphylotrichum]]'' spp. *''[[Stereum hirsutum]]'' *''[[Stictis radiata]]'' *''[[Thelebolus microsporus]]'' *''[[Trichophyton eboreum]]'' {{div col end}}
===Lichens=== Macrolichens (e.g., ''[[Usnea sphacelata]]'', ''[[Usnea antarctica|U. antarctica]]'', ''[[Umbilicaria decussate]]'', and ''[[Usnea aprina|U. aprina]]'') and communities of weakly or non-nitrophilous lichens (e.g., ''[[Pseudephebe minuscula]]'', ''[[Rhizocarpon superficial]]'', and ''[[Rhizocarpon geographicum|R. geographicum]]'', and several species of ''[[Acarospora]]'' and ''[[Buellia]]'') are relatively widespread in coastal ice-free areas.<ref name="adams" /> Sites with substrates influenced by seabirds are colonized by well-developed communities of nitrophilous lichen species such as ''[[Caloplaca athallina]]'', ''[[Caloplaca citrina|C. citrina]]'', ''[[Candelariella flava]]'', ''[[Lecanora expectans]]'', ''[[Physcia caesia]]'', ''[[Rhizoplaca melanophthalma]]'', ''[[Xanthoria elegans]]'', and ''[[Xanthoria mawsonii|X. mawsonii]]''.<ref name="adams" /> In the [[McMurdo Dry Valleys|Dry Valleys]] the normally [[Lithophyte|epilithic]] lichen species (''[[Acarospora gwynnii]]'', ''[[Buellia frigida]]'', ''[[Buellia grisea|B. grisea]]'', ''[[Buelliapallida|B. pallida]]'', ''[[Carbonea vorticosa]]'', ''[[Lecanora fuscobrunnea]]'', ''[[Lecanora cancriformis|L. cancriformis]]'', and ''[[Lecidella siplei]]'') are found primarily in protected [[Ecological niche|niches]] beneath the rock surface occupying a [[Endolith#Subdefinitions|cryptoendolithic]] ecological niche.<ref name="adams" /> [[Lichen]] species identified in recent research:<ref name="adams" />
{{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Acarospora]]'' spp. **''[[Acarospora gwynnii]]'' *''[[Buellia]]'' spp. **''[[Buellia frigida]]'' **''[[Buellia grisea]]'' **''[[Buellia pallida]]'' *''[[Caloplaca athallina]]'' *''[[Caloplaca citrina]]'' *''[[Candelariella flava]]'' *''[[Carbonea vorticosa]]'' (form. ''[[Carbonea capsulata]]'') *''[[Lecanora cancriformis]]'' *''[[Lecanora expectans]]'' *''[[Lecanora fuscobrunnea]]'' *''[[Lecidella siplei]]'' (form. ''[[Lecidea siplei]]'') *''[[Physcia caesia]]'' *''[[Pseudephebe minuscula]]'' *''[[Rhizocarpon geographicum]]'' *''[[Rhizocarpon superficial]]'' *''[[Rhizoplaca melanophthalma]]'' *''[[Umbilicaria aprina]]'' *''[[Umbilicaria decussate]]'' *''[[Usnea antarctica]]'' *''[[Usnea sphacelata]]'' *''[[Xanthoria elegans]]'' *''[[Xanthoria mawsonii]]'' {{div col end}}
===Yeast=== [[Yeast]] species identified in recent research:<ref name="adams" /> {{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Aureobasidium pullulans]]'' *''[[Candida (fungus)|Candida]]'' spp. **''[[Candida psychrophilia]]'' *''[[Cryptococcus]]'' spp. **''[[Cryptococcus albidus]]'' **''[[Cryptococcus foliicola]]'' **''[[Cryptococcus victoriae]]'' **''[[Cryptococcus vishniacii]]'' *''[[Debaryomyces hansenii]]'' *''[[Leucosporidium antarcticum]]'' *''[[Leucosporidium scottii]]'' *''[[Rhodotorula]]'' spp. **''[[Rhodotorula laryngis]]'' **''[[Rhodotorula minuta]]'' **''[[Rhodotorula rubra]]'' **''[[Rhodotorula slooffiae]]'' *''[[Trichosporon]]'' spp. **''[[Trichosporon beigelii]]'' **''[[Trichosporon cutaneum]]'' {{div col end}}
==Mosses== The moss species ''[[Campylopus pyriformis]]'' is restricted to [[Geothermal gradient|geothermal]] sites.<ref name="adams" />
[[Moss]] species identified in recent research:<ref name="adams" /> {{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Anomobryum subrotundifolium]]'' *''[[Bryoerythrophyllum recurvirostre]]'' *''[[Bryum anomobryum]]'' *''[[Bryum pseudotriquetrum]]'' *''[[Campylopus pryiformis]]'' *''[[Cephaloziella varians]]'' *''[[Ceratodon purpureus]]'' *''[[Didymodon brachyphyllus]]'' *''[[Grimmia plagiopodia]]'' *''[[Hennediella heimii]]'' *''[[Pohlia nutans]]'' *''[[Sarconeurum glaciale]]'' *''[[Schistidium antarctici]]'' (form. ''[[Grimmia antarctici]]'') *''[[Syntrichia princeps]]'' {{div col end}}
==Protozoa== The small [[amoeba]]e are of two types. The most abundant are ''[[Acanthamoeba]]'' and ''[[Echinamoeba]]''.<ref name="adams" /> The second group consists of monopodal, worm-like amoebae, the [[subcylindrical]] ''[[Hartmannella]]'' and ''[[Saccamoeba]]'', and the [[Lingulata|lingulate]] ''[[Platyamoeba stenopodia]]'' Page.<ref name="adams" />
[[Amoeboid|Amoebae]] species identified in recent research:<ref name="adams" /> {{div col|colwidth=20em}} *''[[Acanthamoeba]]'' spp. *''[[Echinamoeba]]'' spp. *''[[Hartmannella]]'' spp. *''[[Platyamoeba stenopodia]]'' *''[[Saccamoeba]]'' spp. {{div col end}}
