}}
'''Börse Stuttgart''' (SWB) is a [[stock exchange]] in [[Germany]], the second largest in the country and the ninth largest in Europe.<ref>{{cite web | title = Börse Stuttgart – Die führende Privatanlegerbörse | publisher = Medien Gruppe Kirk AG | url = http://ebn24.com/index.php?id=35647 | accessdate = 30 January 2013}}</ref>
==Structure of Börse Stuttgart Group== * Börse Stuttgart Holding GmbH<ref>{{cite web | title = Boerse Stuttgart Holding GmbH | publisher = Boerse Stuttgart AG | url = https://www.boerse-stuttgart.de/en/aboutboersestuttgart/boersestuttgartgroup/boersestuttgartholdinggmbh/boersestuttgartholdinggmbh.html | accessdate = 30 January 2013 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110911001052/https://www.boerse-stuttgart.de/en/aboutboersestuttgart/boersestuttgartgroup/boersestuttgartholdinggmbh/boersestuttgartholdinggmbh.html | archivedate = 11 September 2011 | df = }}</ref> * Baden-Wuerttembergische Wertpapierboerse GmbH<ref>{{cite web | title = Baden-Wuerttembergische Wertpapierboerse | publisher = Boerse Stuttgart AG | url = https://www.boerse-stuttgart.de/en/aboutboersestuttgart/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerse/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerse.html | accessdate = 30 January 2013 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121123082117/https://www.boerse-stuttgart.de/en/aboutboersestuttgart/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerse/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerse.html | archivedate = 23 November 2012 | df = }}</ref> * Baden-Wuerttembergische Wertpapierboerse e.V.<ref>{{cite web | title = Baden-Wuerttembergische Wertpapierboerse e.V. association | publisher = Boerse Stuttgart AG | url = https://www.boerse-stuttgart.de/en/aboutboersestuttgart/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerseevassociation/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerseevassociation.html | accessdate = 30 January 2013 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110911001033/https://www.boerse-stuttgart.de/en/aboutboersestuttgart/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerseevassociation/baden-wuerttembergischewertpapierboerseevassociation.html | archivedate = 11 September 2011 | df = }}</ref>
==History== Börse Stuttgart came into existence on 4 February 1860, when a group of people from different industries decided to meet regularly. The first such meeting occurred on 12 March 1860.<ref>{{Cite journal | last = Worlitzer | first = K. | authorlink = Karl Worlitzer | title = Die Stuttgarter Industriebörse | journal = Magazin für Kaufleute | volume = 14 | issue = 1 | pages = 263–267 | publisher = Verlag von Wilhelm Rübling | location = Stuttgart & Leipzig | year = 1865 | language = German | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=PkYoAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA265&dq=börse+stuttgart+königsbau&hl=de&ei=6-8fTqSTCoWZOpC4zLUD&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=7&ved=0CEwQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=industriebörse%20zu%20stuttgart&f=false}}</ref> After changing location several times, the exchange is now located in Carl Eugen Bau.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Stock Exchange |publisher=Stuttgart Marketing GmbH |url=http://www.stuttgart-tourist.de/ENG/sights_attractions/boerse_stuttgart.htm |accessdate=22 July 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/60N0ZVhms?url=http://www.stuttgart-tourist.de/ENG/sights_attractions/boerse_stuttgart.htm |archivedate=22 July 2011 |df= }}</ref>
In 2005, Börse Stuttgart, in cooperation with [[ZertifikateJournal-Unternehmensgruppe]], launched S-BOX, a collection of differently themed indices.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Börse Stuttgart und ZertifikateJournal gründen gemeinsame Index-Familie S-BOX |publisher=NetSkill AG |url=http://www.competence-site.de/Boerse-Stuttgart-ZertifikateJournal-gruenden-gemeinsame-Index-Familie-BOX |accessdate=26 July 2011 |language=German |trans-title=Börse Stuttgart and ZertifikateJournal establish joint index family S-BOX |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/60SxDMA2H?url=http://www.competence-site.de/Boerse-Stuttgart-ZertifikateJournal-gruenden-gemeinsame-Index-Familie-BOX |archivedate=26 July 2011 |df= }}</ref>
Since late 2007, Börse Stuttgart holds an 82.4 percent stake in EUWAX AG.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Gruppe Börse Stuttgart: Übernahme der Aktien von EUWAX AG-Gründern Bruker und Schnabel durch Börsenvereinigung abgeschlossen |publisher=DGAP |date=2007-12-13 |url=http://www.dgap.de/news/corporate/gruppe-boerse-stuttgart-uebernahme-der-aktien-von-euwax-aggruendern-bruker-und-schnabel-durch-boersenvereinigung-abgeschlossen_985_190819.htm |accessdate=15 June 2011 |language=German |trans-title=Börse Stuttgart Group: Acquisition of the shares of EUWAX AG founders Bruker and Schnabel by stock exchange organization completed |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111005215005/http://www.dgap.de/news/corporate/gruppe-boerse-stuttgart-uebernahme-der-aktien-von-euwax-aggruendern-bruker-und-schnabel-durch-boersenvereinigung-abgeschlossen_985_190819.htm |archivedate=5 October 2011 |df= }} </ref> In November 2008, Börse Stuttgart Holding GmbH acquired Nordic Growth Market NGM AB, the second largest stock exchange in Sweden.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Boerse Stuttgart subsidiary expands to Norway - Derivatives segment of the Nordic Growth Market (NGM) introduces trading in securitised derivatives in Norway |publisher=Mondo Visione |date=2011-05-13 |url=http://www.mondovisione.com/media-and-resources/news/boerse-stuttgart-subsidiary-expands-to-norway-derivatives-segment-of-the-nordi/ |accessdate=23 June 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5zdyXrzaz?url=http://www.mondovisione.com/media-and-resources/news/boerse-stuttgart-subsidiary-expands-to-norway-derivatives-segment-of-the-nordi/ |archivedate=23 June 2011 |df= }} </ref> T.I.Q.S. GmbH & Co. KG, a joint venture of Börse Stuttgart AG and EUWAX AG developed the T.I.Q.S. (Trading, Information and Quote System), an [[Over-the-counter (finance)|OTC]] trading platform.<ref>{{Cite book | last = Nesnov | first = H. | authorlink = Heike Nesnov |author2=R. Nesnov | title = Outsourcing der Wertpapierabwicklung. Eine Untersuchung aus der Sicht einer Direktbank | publisher = GRIN Verlag | volume = 1 | year = 2003 | page = 36 | language = German | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=Q-MpzIXt0Z0C&pg=PA36&dq=t.i.q.s+gmbh+co+kg&hl=de&ei=9JACTtPeH86aOujQsIQH&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCsQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=t.i.q.s%20gmbh%20co%20kg&f=false | isbn = 978-3-638-72826-3}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book | last = von Böhlen | first = A. | authorlink = Andreas von Böhlen |author2=Kan, J. | title = MiFID-Kompendium: Praktischer Leitfaden für Finanzdienstleister | publisher = Springer-Verlag | year = 2008 | page = 269 | language = German | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=O2Hnpp3j-boC&pg=PA269&dq=t.i.q.s+gmbh+co+kg&hl=de&ei=9JACTtPeH86aOujQsIQH&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=t.i.q.s%20gmbh%20co%20kg&f=false | doi = 10.1007/978-3-540-78816-4 | isbn = 978-3-540-78815-7}}</ref> In 2010, the bourse started Bondm, a trading segment for [[SME finance|SME bonds]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Schaaf |first=S. |authorlink=Stefan Schaaf |title=Rückschlag für Mittelstandsanleihen |publisher=Börse Online |date=2011-07-14 |url=http://www.boerse-online.de/anleihen/nachrichten/meldungen/:Unternehmensanleihen--Rueckschlag-fuer-Mittelstandsanleihen/627389.html |accessdate=15 July 2011 |language=German |trans-title=Setback for SME bonds |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/60BwFgFps?url=http://www.boerse-online.de/anleihen/nachrichten/meldungen/%3AUnternehmensanleihen--Rueckschlag-fuer-Mittelstandsanleihen/627389.html |archivedate=15 July 2011 |df= }}</ref>
