[[File:Frederiksgade (Aarhus).JPG|thumb|Frederiksgade in Aarhus is a part of the route]] '''Danish national cycle route 5''', known as the ''Østkystruten'' (East Coast Route), is the fifth of the 11 [[Danish National Cycle Routes]]. It runs from [[Sønderborg ]] in [[Southern Jutland]] to [[Skagen]], the northernmost tip of [[Jutland]] in the [[Northern Jutland]] region. It follows the east coast of [[Jutland]] and is {{convert|650|km|mi|abbr=on}} long, with 90% of this distance being along paved roads.
