'''Zephirium''' is a [[titular Bishop]]ric of the [[Roman Catholic Church]] located in [[Cilicia]].<ref>Joseph Bingham, Origines Ecclesiasticæ: The Antiquities of the Christian Church, Volume 1 (H.G. Bohn, 1846)p94.</ref>
There are five known [[bishop]]s of the [[Cathedra|Seat]].
*Hypatus, attended the [[Council of Chalcedon]].<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com.au/books?id=6IUaOOT1G3UC&pg=RA1-PA81&lpg=RA1-PA81&dq|title=The Acts of the Council of Chalcedon|volume=1|editor-first1=Richard|editor-last1=Price|editor-first2=Michael|editor-last2=Gaddis|publisher=Liverpool University Press|year=2005|isbn=0-85323-039-0|page=81|via=Google Books}}</ref> *Zenobus,<ref>Adam M. Schor, Theodoret's People: Social Networks and Religious Conflict in Late Roman Syria (University of California Press, 17 May 2011) p94].</ref> an associate of [[Theodoret]] of [[Cyrrhus]] *[[Jean-Jacques Crouzet]] (1 Oct 1888 Appointed - 8 Jan 1933).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bcrou.html|title= Bishop Jean-Jacques Crouzet|website=catholic-hierarchy.org|accessdate=2018-08-11}}</ref> *[[Antonín Eltschkner|Antonin Eltschkner]] (10 Feb 1933 Appointed - 22 Feb 1961)<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/belts.html Bishop Antonin Eltschkner ].</ref> *[[André Collini]] (7 Sep 1962 Appointed - 26 Jul 1966) ==References== {{reflist}}
